main event: A civilian witness sighted an unidentified object in the sky over Westhampton Beach, New York on August 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as a football-shaped, bright orange object tilted at a 45-degree angle.
The object was observed for 6-7 minutes, traveling from Riverhead to Westhampton Beach.
The witness was a photographer for the local newspaper, the Riverhead News Review.
Weather conditions at the time included a surface wind of 0 knots, with higher winds aloft.
No radar sighting or aircraft intercept was reported, and the sighting was concluded as a probable civilian aircraft operating VFR.
